      "blocks": {
        "faq_RBwrTX": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How much watts can I save with sockeloen aero socks?",
            "answer": "<p>The watt saving you can achieve compared to normal socks can <strong>be between 5 and 15 watts</strong>, depending on speed, jaw angle, body shape and total cda. In our research we normally measure total cda and the % of change on your total cda.</p>",
            "metafield_key": "",
            "metafield_fallback": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_Y8JLka": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Which sockheight are these sockeloen aero socks?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>This sock in [metafield] high. </strong>We optimized our fitt for the perfect looking sockheight on the bike. Chek our <a href=\"/pages/size-guide\" title=\"Size Guide\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>full size guide</strong></span></a><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong> </strong></span>to read exactly how we measure.</p>",
            "metafield_key": "custom.height",
            "metafield_fallback": "19cm"
          }
        },
        "faq_9RzfCj": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What if I am between sizes of the aero socks?",
            "answer": "<p>Our socks come in 36-42 and 43-48 or one size(39-46). If you're between sizes, we recommend sizing up for a more comfortable fit. Check our <a href=\"/pages/size-guide\" title=\"Size Guide\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>size guide</strong></span></a> for detailed measurements.</p>",
            "metafield_key": "",
            "metafield_fallback": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_7idmHH": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What material are Sockeloen aero socks made of?",
            "answer": "<p>The top layers of our aero socks can be an aerodynamic lycra yarn (classic aero sock) or a woven aerodynamic material (fastest socks on the planet). The foot part of these aero socks are made from a premium blend of [metafield], polypropylene, and elastane. </p>",
            "metafield_key": "custom.materials",
            "metafield_fallback": "Q-Skin"
          }
        },
        "faq_YhiEwH": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How should I wash my sockeloen aerodynamic socks?",
            "answer": "<p>Machine wash at 30°C inside out. Avoid fabric softener and tumble dryer. This impasts the anti slip heavily and significantly reduces lifetime of your aero socks.</p>",
            "metafield_key": "",
            "metafield_fallback": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_NLxUKi": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do Sockeloen socks last?",
            "answer": "<p>With proper care, (no tumble drying or softner) our socks typically last 1-2 years of regular use. The reinforced heel and toe areas are designed for extra durability.</p>",
            "metafield_key": "",
            "metafield_fallback": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_wRWWf3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why are sockeloen aero socks longer than regular socks?",
            "answer": "<p>Our aero sock material is faster then your skin, so the higher this sock the more aero gains. Most pro cyclists prefer a cuff height between 17 to 21cm depending on their leg length.</p>",
            "metafield_key": "",
            "metafield_fallback": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_JgMmFK": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I use these aero socks for other sports?",
            "answer": "<p>Absolutely! While designed for cycling, our socks perform great for running, hiking, and everyday wear. The moisture-wicking properties and comfortable fit make them versatile for any activity.</p>",
